      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>The <sup>1</sup>H NMR spectrum shown is that of a compound with the formula C<sub>9</sub>H<sub>10</sub>O. How many double bonds and/or rings does this compound contain? If the unknown compound has an IR absorption at 1690 cm<sup>–1</sup>, what is a likely structure?</p>\n<img src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBb1FXIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--69db3a6960436849ad2d5e76b2c510ad3b9328e8/OChem_19_EC_060.jpg\" alt=\"Proton spectrum shows shifts of 0 (T M S), 1.20 (triplet), 2.97 (quartet, 7.39 and 7.56 (multiplet), and 7.97 (doublet). Relative areas are 3.00, 2.00, 2.00, 1.00, and 2.00 respectively.\">",
